{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17616708","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17616708"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:06:49+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:06:49+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16413"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16413","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16413"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.11,0.56,0.19,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9104"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74838"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9104"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16413"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60344"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"32"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"174"},{"type":"tags","id":"1009"},{"type":"tags","id":"1150"},{"type":"tags","id":"1288"},{"type":"tags","id":"1380"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3188"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10378"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21622"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21625"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74838","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74838"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA person presents with progressive cognitive decline. The clinical features include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EParkinsonian motor symptoms\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EVisual hallucinations\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EFluctuating levels of alertness and cognition\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Alzheimer disease","Vascular dementia","Lewy body dementia","Frontotemporal dementia","Wernicke-Korsakoff syndrome"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis presentation is classic for \u003Cstrong\u003ELewy body dementia\u003C/strong\u003E, characterised by the triad of parkinsonism (tremor, rigidity, bradykinesia), visual hallucinations, and fluctuating cognition.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlzheimer disease\u003C/strong\u003E presents with prominent memory impairment and lacks early visual hallucinations or parkinsonism. \u003Cstrong\u003EVascular dementia\u003C/strong\u003E has a stepwise decline with focal neurological deficits corresponding to vascular territories. \u003Cstrong\u003EFrontotemporal dementia\u003C/strong\u003E presents with prominent behavioral or language changes with preserved visuospatial skills. \u003Cstrong\u003EWernicke-Korsakoff syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is caused by thiamine deficiency and presents with confusion, ataxia, and ophthalmoplegia in the acute phase.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe presence of visual hallucinations early in the disease course, combined with parkinsonism and cognitive fluctuations, is highly suggestive of Lewy body dementia. These patients are often extremely sensitive to antipsychotic medications.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lewy body dementia is characterised by the clinical triad of parkinsonism, visual hallucinations, and fluctuating cognition.","Lewy body dementia is the second most common type of neurodegenerative dementia after Alzheimer disease.","The presence of visual hallucinations early in the disease course helps distinguish Lewy body dementia from other types of dementia."],"references":["McKeith IG, Boeve BF, Dickson DW, Halliday G, Taylor JP, Weintraub D, Aarsland D, Galvin J, Attems J, Ballard CG, Bayston A, Beach TG, Blanc F, Bohnen N, Bonanni L, Bras J, Brundin P, Burn D, Chen-Plotkin A, Duda JE, El-Agnaf O, Feldman H, Ferman TJ, Ffytche D, Fujishiro H, Galasko D, Goldman JG, Gomperts SN, Graff-Radford NR, Honig LS, Iranzo A, Kantarci K, Kaufer D, Kukull W, Lee VMY, Leverenz JB, Lewis S, Lippa C, Lunde A, Masellis M, Masliah E, McLean P, Mollenhauer B, Montine TJ, Moreno E, Mori E, Murray M, O\u0027Brien JT, Orimo S, Postuma RB, Ramaswamy S, Ross OA, Salmon DP, Singleton A, Taylor A, Thomas A, Tiraboschi P, Toledo JB, Trojanowski JQ, Tsuang D, Walker Z, Yamada M, Kosaka K. Diagnosis and management of dementia with Lewy bodies: Fourth consensus report of the DLB Consortium. Neurology. 2017 Jul 4;89(1):88-100. doi: 10.1212/WNL.0000000000004058. Epub 2017 Jun 7. PMID: 28592453; PMCID: PMC5496518.","EFERENCES","Gale SA, Acar D, Daffner KR. Dementia. Am J Med. 2018 Oct;131(10):1161-1169. doi: 10.1016/j.amjmed.2018.01.022. Epub 2018 Feb 6. PMID: 29425707","B\u0142aszczyk JW. Pathogenesis of Dementia. Int J Mol Sci. 2022 Dec 29;24(1):543. doi: 10.3390/ijms24010543. PMID: 36613988; PMCID: PMC9820433","Dintica CS, Yaffe K. Epidemiology and Risk Factors for Dementia. Psychiatr Clin North Am. 2022 Dec;45(4):677-689. doi: 10.1016/j.psc.2022.07.011. Epub 2022 Oct 14. PMID: 36396272"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60344"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16413"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60344","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60344"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-27T17:27:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-27T17:27:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9104"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"